[The most common cause of fish die-offs as the one described is reduced oxygen in the water, which in turn may be caused to several factors that might interact among them, such as drought, algae bloom, overpopulation, or an increase in water temperature. According to the text, the most likely origin of this episode is a combination of climatic and limnological factors that predisposed to algal blooms and decay of biological material that depleted the oxygen in the lake. - PMB

